[SN]TITLE[SN]
Oldham Athletic 0-0 Chesterfield

[SN]FIRST-SENTENCE[SN]
Chesterfield took another step towards securing a League One play-off spot despite being held at Oldham.

[SN]RESTBODY[SN]
Oldham's best effort came when Connor Brown's drive had to be turned round the post by Chesterfield's Tommy Lee.
The Spireites created their best chance in the 82nd minute, but Armand Gnanduillet blazed over from close range after a Sam Clucas flick came back off the post.
Oldham hung on to record their third straight draw, and remain in 14th.
Oldham manager Dean Holden told BBC Radio Manchester:
