"For me, it's about remaining calm and there's a staff behind me that have all pulled together and in one direction and we're working every single day to prepare the players properly.
"Whether I'm going to be here next season, or whether I'm not, for me doesn't come into it. I'm giving it everything everyday, as is everybody.
"If the chairman decides to offer me the job, then we'll have a conversation. But I'll control what I'm in control of which is, you know, remaining focused on the next game "
